      "raw_text": "Louis w. Hill, president of the\nGreat Northern, has reached Sc\nattic and expresses his willingness\ntot appear before the State Bar as\nISOLATION commission IL his pres\nence is desired in the Gordon\nRoot investigation. He claims to\nhave knowledge that will be of\nvalue, stating that he had instruct\ned l.. c. Gilman to place in the\nhands of the commission all mat\ntiers of record that would throw any\nlight on the case and that Gilman\nhad done so while the commission\nwas in Spokane.\n\n\n1t is not known whether Gordon\nwill consent to testify before the\ncommission."
    }
